   <body>
      <prereq>
         <indexterm>HMI</indexterm>
         <note>The update of the firmware
on the controller box can be done via a RS232 serial connection.</note>
      </prereq>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Connect your laptop to the service port (J405) located
on the rear side of the front panel (A810).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/location_of_service_port_j405_on_the_rear_side_of_the_front_panel_120mm_0000116570.svg"
                         translate="yes"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Launch the UPS Tuner and select <uicontrol>Display Module</uicontrol>. After start-up, your laptop will automatically log in and the main
menu appears on the terminal screen.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Navigate through the menu tree by typing the number
of the submenu you wish to enter, followed by the <uicontrol>ENTER</uicontrol> key.</note>
            </stepxmp>
            <stepxmp/>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type <uicontrol>5</uicontrol> (<uicontrol>HMI Firmware
Update</uicontrol>).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmia_0000148864.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type <uicontrol>1</uicontrol> to initialize the HMI for
the firmware update, or press the <uicontrol>ESC</uicontrol> key to
abort. After successful initialization, the HMI waits for a new hex
file.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmib_0000148863.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmic_0000148862.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click on <uicontrol>Send file</uicontrol> and browse to
the firmware file on your laptop and click on <uicontrol>Open</uicontrol>. </p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmid_0000148861.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmi1_0000148860.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>After the file transfer, the file checksum will now appear
on the screen. Check if file checksum is correct before continuing.
If the file checksum is not correct, press the <uicontrol>ESC</uicontrol> key.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmi2_0000148859.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Type <uicontrol>y</uicontrol> to confirm the update and
copy the new firmware from the SRAM to the FLASH memory.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>If you wish to cancel the update and keep the old firmware,
press the <uicontrol>ESC</uicontrol> key.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>After the firmware has been successfully updated and <uicontrol>Update done. Restart system...</uicontrol> appears on the screen,
restart the HMI by either unplugging the HMI supply or switch the
system off and then back on.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmi4_0000148858.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
